Describe a person who helps protect the environment
- who this person is
- when you knew him/her
- what he/she does to protect the environment
- how you feel about this person

I’m going to talk about my cousin Linh, someone I really admire for her efforts to protect the environment.

She’s 21 years old and currently studying marketing at university. We’ve been close since childhood because our families live near each other, so we’ve spent a lot of time together over the years.

She became interested in environmental issues about three years ago after watching a documentary on climate change, and since then, she’s made a lot of changes to her lifestyle. For example, she avoids single-use plastics, always carries a reusable water bottle, and brings her own shopping bags when she goes out.

What I find especially impressive is that she doesn’t just change her own habits—she also encourages others to do the same. She often shares simple tips on social media, like how to reduce waste, recycle properly, or save energy at home. Sometimes when we meet, she even reminds me to be more environmentally friendly, which I find really helpful rather than annoying.

Thanks to her influence, I’ve started to become more aware of my own habits, like reducing food waste and using fewer plastic items.

Overall, I feel really proud of her. I think she’s making a positive impact, even through small actions, and she’s definitely inspired me to be more responsible towards the environment.
